Metrorail had suspended all train services earlier following a fire at Cape Town station. CAPE TOWN - Some train services have been restored in Cape Town on Friday morning. Commuters are warned they could face delays of over two hours. Metrorail had suspended all train services earlier following a fire at Cape Town station. READ: Khayelitsha, Mitchell's Plain train services still suspended Train carriages were set alight in the early hours of this morning. A number of passenger coaches were destroyed and the blaze was extinguished just before five am. No injuries have been reported. Commuters are advised to make use of alternative transport. Metrorail says service recovery is under way.